{"slug":"sirkuler-25-0188eng-1","reference":"Sirkuler_25_0188ENG","gazette":"The Official Journal of the EU (OJ L), 2025/395, 24.2.2025","title":"EU Officially Approves 16th Sanction Package Against Russia on February 24, 2025","date":"25 Şubat 2025","bodyHtml":"<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><b>EU Officially Approves 16th Sanctions Package Against\r\nRussia on February 24, 2025</b><o:p></o:p></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\">The European Council officially adopted&nbsp; <a href=\"https://www.consilium.europa.eu/en/press/press-releases/2025/02/24/three-years-of-russia-s-full-scale-invasion-and-war-of-aggression-against-ukraine-eu-adopts-its-16th-package-of-economic-and-individual-measures/\" target=\"_blank\" style=\"text-decoration-line: underline; font-weight: bold;\">the 16th Sanction Package Against Russia </a>on February 24, 2025. This decision includes measures\r\ntargeting key sectors of the Russian economy such as energy, trade,\r\ntransportation, and infrastructure.<o:p></o:p></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\"><a href=\"https://eur-lex.europa.eu/legal-content/EN/TXT/?uri=OJ:L_202500395\" target=\"_blank\" style=\"text-decoration-line: underline; font-weight: bold;\">Click here to access Council Regulation No. 2025/395.</a><o:p></o:p></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\">Regarding trade in goods, you can find the list of newly\r\nsanctioned goods added to the lists at the end of this Circular.<o:p></o:p></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\">An additional company from Turkey has been added to the list\r\nof firms identified as contributing to Russia’s military capacity, bringing the\r\ntotal number of Turkish companies on the list to 11.<o:p></o:p></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\"><b>1. New Sanctions Lists<o:p></o:p></b></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\">A total of 83 individuals and entities involved in\r\nsupporting Russia’s military activities, violating sanctions, operating in\r\ncryptocurrency exchanges, and participating in the maritime sector have been\r\nadded to the sanctions list.<o:p></o:p></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\">A new criterion has been introduced: individuals and\r\nentities linked to or benefiting from Russia’s military-industrial complex can\r\nnow also be included in the sanctions list.<o:p></o:p></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\"><b>2. Trade Measures<o:p></o:p></b></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\"><b>Russian Aluminum Ban:</b> A direct EU ban has been\r\nimposed on the import of primary aluminum from Russia. However, a transition\r\nquota of 275,000 tons, equivalent to 80% of 2024 imports, will be applied.<o:p></o:p></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\"><b>Export Restrictions on Dual-Use Goods:</b> New\r\nrestrictions have been introduced on the export of products such as chemical\r\nprecursors, CNC software, video game controllers used for drones, and\r\nmilitary-grade chromium compounds.<o:p></o:p></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\"><b>Industrial Goods Restrictions:</b> New import bans will\r\napply to minerals, chemicals, steel, glass materials, and fireworks that could\r\nbe used for military purposes.<o:p></o:p></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\"><b>3. Energy Measures<o:p></o:p></b></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\"><b>Oil Storage Ban:</b> The temporary storage of crude oil\r\nor petroleum products from Russia in EU ports or their placement in free trade\r\nzones has been prohibited.<o:p></o:p></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\"><b>LNG and Crude Oil Project Ban:</b> Restrictions on\r\nRussian crude oil projects, such as Vostok, have been expanded.<o:p></o:p></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\"><b>4. Transportation Measures<o:p></o:p></b></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\"><b>Expanded Flight Ban:</b> Sanctions have been imposed on\r\nthird-country airlines conducting domestic flights within Russia or supplying\r\naviation products to Russian airlines.<o:p></o:p></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\"><b>Land Transport Restrictions:</b> The share that Russians\r\ncan hold in EU transport companies has been limited to 25%, closing sanction\r\nloopholes.<o:p></o:p></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\"><b>5. Infrastructure Measures<o:p></o:p></b></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\"><b>Transaction Ban on Russian Infrastructure:</b> Moscow's\r\nVnukovo and Zhukovsky airports, along with four regional airports, major ports,\r\nand critical transportation hubs, have been targeted.<o:p></o:p></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\"><b>EU Construction Services Ban:</b> EU companies are now\r\nprohibited from participating in construction projects in Russia.<o:p></o:p></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\"><b>6. Financial Sector Measures<o:p></o:p></b></p><ul style=\"margin-top:0cm\" type=\"disc\">\r\n <li class=\"MsoNormal\">13\r\n     financial institutions have been banned from using specialized financial\r\n     messaging services.<o:p></o:p></li>\r\n <li class=\"MsoNormal\">3\r\n     banks using Russia’s SPFS system to evade sanctions have been subjected to\r\n     transaction bans.<o:p></o:p></li>\r\n <li class=\"MsoNormal\">Restrictions\r\n     on financial institutions and crypto asset providers violating the oil\r\n     price cap have been expanded.<o:p></o:p></li>\r\n</ul><p class=\"MsoNormal\"><b>7. Measures Against Sanctions Evasion<o:p></o:p></b></p><ul style=\"margin-top:0cm\" type=\"disc\">\r\n <li class=\"MsoNormal\">An\r\n     additional 74 vessels involved in Russia's shadow fleet activities and\r\n     contributing to its energy revenues have been sanctioned, bringing the\r\n     total number to 153.<o:p></o:p></li>\r\n <li class=\"MsoNormal\">A\r\n     new listing criterion has been introduced to sanction individuals and\r\n     entities supporting unsafe oil tankers.<o:p></o:p></li>\r\n <li class=\"MsoNormal\">53\r\n     additional companies—34 of them outside Russia—have been subjected to\r\n     export restrictions for supporting Russia’s military activities or\r\n     violating sanctions.<o:p></o:p></li>\r\n</ul><p class=\"MsoNormal\">The list of prohibited goods and technologies that cannot be\r\nsold, supplied, transferred, or exported—directly or indirectly—to any natural\r\nor legal person, entity, or body in Russia, including Russia’s Exclusive\r\nEconomic Zone and Continental Shelf, has been expanded to include <b>\"software\"\r\nused in oil and gas exploration.</b><o:p></o:p></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\"><b>The newly banned \"software\" includes:<o:p></o:p></b></p><ul style=\"margin-top:0cm\" type=\"disc\">\r\n <li class=\"MsoNormal\"><b>Software</b>\r\n     for reservoir discovery and calculation<o:p></o:p></li>\r\n <li class=\"MsoNormal\"><b>Software</b>\r\n     for the calculation, processing, and analysis of seismic data<o:p></o:p></li>\r\n <li class=\"MsoNormal\"><b>Software</b>\r\n     for geological visual inspections and related\r\n     characterization/modeling/visualization/calculations<o:p></o:p></li>\r\n <li class=\"MsoNormal\"><b>Drilling\r\n     software</b>, planning software for drilling processes, trajectory\r\n     software for drilling processes<o:p></o:p></li>\r\n <li class=\"MsoNormal\"><b>Software</b>\r\n     for inertial navigation systems used in drilling<o:p></o:p></li>\r\n <li class=\"MsoNormal\"><b>Real-time\r\n     well monitoring software</b><o:p></o:p></li>\r\n <li class=\"MsoNormal\"><b>Software</b>\r\n     for monitoring and maintaining oil and gas production<o:p></o:p></li>\r\n</ul><p class=\"MsoNormal\"><b>Newly Banned Imports from Russia:<o:p></o:p></b></p><p>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n</p><p class=\"MsoNormal\"><b>7601 - Unwrought Aluminum</b></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\">Items added to or expanded in the list of goods prohibited for export to Russia;</p><table class=\"MsoNormalTable\" border=\"1\" cellspacing=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\" width=\"100%\" style=\"background: white; width: 858.85px; border: none;\"><tbody><tr><td valign=\"top\" style=\"padding: 0cm; border: 1pt solid black;\"><p class=\"MsoNormal\" align=\"center\" style=\"margin: 3pt 9.75pt 3pt 0cm; text-align: center; line-height: 15.6pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, serif;\">2518<o:p></o:p></span></p></td><td valign=\"top\" style=\"padding: 0cm; border-top: 1pt solid black; border-right: 1pt solid black; border-bottom: 1pt solid black; border-image: initial; border-left: none;\"><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 3pt 0cm; line-height: 15.6pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, serif;\">Dolomite, whether or not calcined or sintered, including dolomite roughly trimmed or merely cut, by sawing or otherwise, into blocks or slabs of a&nbsp;rectangular (including square) shape<o:p></o:p></span></p></td></tr><tr><td valign=\"top\" style=\"padding: 0cm; border-right: 1pt solid black; border-bottom: 1pt solid black; border-left: 1pt solid black; border-image: initial; border-top: none;\"><p class=\"MsoNormal\" align=\"center\" style=\"margin: 3pt 9.75pt 3pt 0cm; text-align: center; line-height: 15.6pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, serif;\">2519<o:p></o:p></span></p></td><td valign=\"top\" style=\"padding: 0cm; border-top: none; border-left: none; border-bottom: 1pt solid black; border-right: 1pt solid black;\"><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 3pt 0cm; line-height: 15.6pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, serif;\">Natural magnesium carbonate (magnesite); fused magnesia; dead-burned \"sintered\" magnesia, whether or not containing small quantities of other oxides added before sintering; other magnesium oxide, whether or not pure<o:p></o:p></span></p></td></tr><tr><td valign=\"top\" style=\"padding: 0cm; border-right: 1pt solid black; border-bottom: 1pt solid black; border-left: 1pt solid black; border-image: initial; border-top: none;\"><p class=\"MsoNormal\" align=\"center\" style=\"margin: 3pt 9.75pt 3pt 0cm; text-align: center; line-height: 15.6pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, serif;\">2520<o:p></o:p></span></p></td><td valign=\"top\" style=\"padding: 0cm; border-top: none; border-left: none; border-bottom: 1pt solid black; border-right: 1pt solid black;\"><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 3pt 0cm; line-height: 15.6pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, serif;\">Gypsum; anhydrite; plasters consisting of calcined gypsum or calcium sulphate, whether or not coloured, with or without small quantities of accelerators or retarders<o:p></o:p></span></p></td></tr><tr><td valign=\"top\" style=\"padding: 0cm; border-right: 1pt solid black; border-bottom: 1pt solid black; border-left: 1pt solid black; border-image: initial; border-top: none;\"><p class=\"MsoNormal\" align=\"center\" style=\"margin: 3pt 9.75pt 3pt 0cm; text-align: center; line-height: 15.6pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, serif;\">2615<o:p></o:p></span></p></td><td valign=\"top\" style=\"padding: 0cm; border-top: none; border-left: none; border-bottom: 1pt solid black; border-right: 1pt solid black;\"><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 3pt 0cm; line-height: 15.6pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, serif;\">Niobium, tantalum, vanadium or zirconium ores and concentrates<o:p></o:p></span></p></td></tr><tr><td valign=\"top\" style=\"padding: 0cm; border-right: 1pt solid black; border-bottom: 1pt solid black; border-left: 1pt solid black; border-image: initial; border-top: none;\"><p class=\"MsoNormal\" align=\"center\" style=\"margin: 3pt 9.75pt 3pt 0cm; text-align: center; line-height: 15.6pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, serif;\">2834<o:p></o:p></span></p></td><td valign=\"top\" style=\"padding: 0cm; border-top: none; border-left: none; border-bottom: 1pt solid black; border-right: 1pt solid black;\"><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 3pt 0cm; line-height: 15.6pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, serif;\">Nitrites; nitrates<o:p></o:p></span></p></td></tr><tr><td valign=\"top\" style=\"padding: 0cm; border-right: 1pt solid black; border-bottom: 1pt solid black; border-left: 1pt solid black; border-image: initial; border-top: none;\"><p class=\"MsoNormal\" align=\"center\" style=\"margin: 3pt 9.75pt 3pt 0cm; text-align: center; line-height: 15.6pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, serif;\">3604<o:p></o:p></span></p></td><td valign=\"top\" style=\"padding: 0cm; border-top: none; border-left: none; border-bottom: 1pt solid black; border-right: 1pt solid black;\"><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 3pt 0cm; line-height: 15.6pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, serif;\">Fireworks, signalling flares, rain rockets, fog signals and other pyrotechnic articles<o:p></o:p></span></p></td></tr><tr><td valign=\"top\" style=\"padding: 0cm; border-right: 1pt solid black; border-bottom: 1pt solid black; border-left: 1pt solid black; border-image: initial; border-top: none;\"><p class=\"MsoNormal\" align=\"center\" style=\"margin: 3pt 9.75pt 3pt 0cm; text-align: center; line-height: 15.6pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, serif;\">3605<o:p></o:p></span></p></td><td valign=\"top\" style=\"padding: 0cm; border-top: none; border-left: none; border-bottom: 1pt solid black; border-right: 1pt solid black;\"><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 3pt 0cm; line-height: 15.6pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, serif;\">Matches, other than pyrotechnic articles of heading 3604<o:p></o:p></span></p></td></tr><tr><td valign=\"top\" style=\"padding: 0cm; border-right: 1pt solid black; border-bottom: 1pt solid black; border-left: 1pt solid black; border-image: initial; border-top: none;\"><p class=\"MsoNormal\" align=\"center\" style=\"margin: 3pt 9.75pt 3pt 0cm; text-align: center; line-height: 15.6pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, serif;\">3606<o:p></o:p></span></p></td><td valign=\"top\" style=\"padding: 0cm; border-top: none; border-left: none; border-bottom: 1pt solid black; border-right: 1pt solid black;\"><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 3pt 0cm; line-height: 15.6pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, serif;\">Ferro-cerium and other pyrophoric alloys in all forms; articles of combustible materials as specified in note 2 to Chapter&nbsp;36<o:p></o:p></span></p></td></tr><tr><td valign=\"top\" style=\"padding: 0cm; border-right: 1pt solid black; border-bottom: 1pt solid black; border-left: 1pt solid black; border-image: initial; border-top: none;\"><p class=\"MsoNormal\" align=\"center\" style=\"margin: 3pt 9.75pt 3pt 0cm; text-align: center; line-height: 15.6pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, serif;\">3827&nbsp;90<o:p></o:p></span></p></td><td valign=\"top\" style=\"padding: 0cm; border-top: none; border-left: none; border-bottom: 1pt solid black; border-right: 1pt solid black;\"><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 3pt 0cm; line-height: 15.6pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, serif;\">Mixtures containing halogenated derivatives of methane, ethane or propane, not else specified in other sub-headings pertaining to Heading 3827<o:p></o:p></span></p></td></tr><tr><td valign=\"top\" style=\"padding: 0cm; border-right: 1pt solid black; border-bottom: 1pt solid black; border-left: 1pt solid black; border-image: initial; border-top: none;\"><p class=\"MsoNormal\" align=\"center\" style=\"margin: 3pt 9.75pt 3pt 0cm; text-align: center; line-height: 15.6pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, serif;\">4811<o:p></o:p></span></p></td><td valign=\"top\" style=\"padding: 0cm; border-top: none; border-left: none; border-bottom: 1pt solid black; border-right: 1pt solid black;\"><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 3pt 0cm; line-height: 15.6pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, serif;\">Paper, paperboard, cellulose wadding and webs of cellulose fibres, coated, impregnated, covered, surface-coloured, surface-decorated or printed, in rolls or in square or rectangular sheets, of any size, other than goods of heading 4803 , 4809 and 4810<o:p></o:p></span></p></td></tr><tr><td valign=\"top\" style=\"padding: 0cm; border-right: 1pt solid black; border-bottom: 1pt solid black; border-left: 1pt solid black; border-image: initial; border-top: none;\"><p class=\"MsoNormal\" align=\"center\" style=\"margin: 3pt 9.75pt 3pt 0cm; text-align: center; line-height: 15.6pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, serif;\">6814<o:p></o:p></span></p></td><td valign=\"top\" style=\"padding: 0cm; border-top: none; border-left: none; border-bottom: 1pt solid black; border-right: 1pt solid black;\"><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 3pt 0cm; line-height: 15.6pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, serif;\">Worked mica and articles of mica, including agglomerated or reconstituted mica, whether or not on a&nbsp;support of paper, paperboard or other materials<o:p></o:p></span></p></td></tr><tr><td valign=\"top\" style=\"padding: 0cm; border-right: 1pt solid black; border-bottom: 1pt solid black; border-left: 1pt solid black; border-image: initial; border-top: none;\"><p class=\"MsoNormal\" align=\"center\" style=\"margin: 3pt 9.75pt 3pt 0cm; text-align: center; line-height: 15.6pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, serif;\">7007<o:p></o:p></span></p></td><td valign=\"top\" style=\"padding: 0cm; border-top: none; border-left: none; border-bottom: 1pt solid black; border-right: 1pt solid black;\"><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 3pt 0cm; line-height: 15.6pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, serif;\">Safety glass, consisting of toughened (tempered), or laminated glass<o:p></o:p></span></p></td></tr><tr><td valign=\"top\" style=\"padding: 0cm; border-right: 1pt solid black; border-bottom: 1pt solid black; border-left: 1pt solid black; border-image: initial; border-top: none;\"><p class=\"MsoNormal\" align=\"center\" style=\"margin: 3pt 9.75pt 3pt 0cm; text-align: center; line-height: 15.6pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, serif;\">7320<o:p></o:p></span></p></td><td valign=\"top\" style=\"padding: 0cm; border-top: none; border-left: none; border-bottom: 1pt solid black; border-right: 1pt solid black;\"><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 3pt 0cm; line-height: 15.6pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, serif;\">Springs and leaves for spring, of iron or steel<o:p></o:p></span></p></td></tr></tbody></table><p class=\"MsoNormal\"><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\"><o:p>Items added to the list of goods that are prohibited from being sold, supplied, transferred, or exported, directly or indirectly, to any natural or legal person, entity, or body in Russia, or for use in Russia, as they may contribute to the development of Russia's industrial capacities:</o:p></p><table class=\"MsoNormalTable\" border=\"1\" cellspacing=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\" width=\"100%\" style=\"background: white; width: 858.85px; border: none;\"><tbody><tr><td valign=\"top\" style=\"padding: 0cm; border: 1pt solid black;\"><p class=\"MsoNormal\" align=\"center\" style=\"margin: 3pt 9.75pt 3pt 0cm; text-align: center; line-height: 15.6pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, serif;\">3811&nbsp;90<o:p></o:p></span></p></td><td valign=\"top\" style=\"padding: 0cm; border-top: 1pt solid black; border-right: 1pt solid black; border-bottom: 1pt solid black; border-image